The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 September is 73,482 (8,469.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 September, there were 1,482 new confirmed cases (170.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 September, there were 2,090 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (608 fewer cases).
